subject: It's great to hear from you!
html:
Hello Eli!

Thank you for your interest in the fully online Security Studies: Online - Bachelor of Arts program. 

We are here to assist you with any questions you may have about the program and the process you need to follow to get started.

This degree aims to give students a solid grasp of 21st-century national and international security challenges. The curriculum focuses on four major areas: cybersecurity, homeland security, security operations, and intelligence and national security, and provides a solid foundation of theory plus the critical thinking skills needed for success in the field.

The online format is convenient and accessible from anywhere so you have the flexibility you need. You can get more information about by downloading our program brochure.

 
In today's increasingly competitive world, higher education is often the key to a better life. However, being a full-time college student attending classes on campus is no longer a possibility for many people who need to keep working or who have family obligations that prevent them from coming to campus. These are the studentslike youthat we serve. Our goal is to make getting an education possible no matter where you are, so you can fit learning into your life and secure a better future for yourself and your family. And thanks to online learning, we can make this possible.

We also know that you may be nervous about being an online student. What if you need help? Have questions? We understand. Our unique hands-on approach to student support means that the second you contacted us, you (and every one of our online students) were assigned an enrollment counselor to help you with the application process. I am your enrollment counselor. 

Please do not hesitate to contact me to further discuss your interest and get answers to any questions you may have.  You may contact me via email at utepconnect@utep.edu or by phone at . You can also schedule a phone appointment via our Appointment Link: 

Thank you and go Miners!

David Montgomery

UTEP Connect - Extended University
The University of Texas at El Paso
Phone: 915.747.6551 / 1.800.684.8837
Email: utepconnect@utep.edu
Visit our website!
